'From Squeak3.7beta of ''1 April 2004'' [latest update: #5868] on 2 April 2004 at 7:43:41 pm'!"Change Set:		KeyFocusChange-dgdDate:			2 April 2004Author:			Diego Gomez Deck <DiegoGomezDeck@ConsultAr.com>Fix a bug introduced in 5849TextMorphSelectionFix-rr that causes an error when an TextMorph has not a paragraph.To force the bug, try to change any value (for example: heading) in an eToy viewer."!!TextMorph methodsFor: 'event handling' stamp: 'dgd 4/2/2004 19:40'!keyboardFocusChange: aBoolean 	"rr 3/21/2004 22:55 : removed the #ifFalse: branch, 	which was responsible of the deselection of text when the 	paragraph lost focus. This way selection works in a more standard 	way, and this permits the menu keyboard control to be really effective"	paragraph isNil ifFalse:[paragraph focused: aBoolean].	aBoolean 		ifTrue: 			["A hand is wanting to send us characters..."			self hasFocus ifFalse: [self editor	"Forces install"]].	self changed.! !